    </para>
    <para id="import-auto-id2491579">
     <emphasis effect="italics">
Coral reefs
     </emphasis>
are found in the warm, clear, shallow waters of tropical oceans around islands
or along continental coastlines. They are mostly formed from calcium carbonate
produced by living coral. Reefs provide food and shelter for other organisms
and protect shorelines from erosion.
    </para>
    <figure id="import-auto-id2486373">
     <media id="import-auto-id2486374" alt="">
