   <section id="import-auto-id2487143">
    <title>
Grassland
    </title>
    <para id="import-auto-id2456413">
Grasslands cover regions where moderate rainfall is sufficient for the growth of
grasses, but not enough for stands of trees. There are two main types of
grasslands:
     <emphasis effect="italics">
tropical grasslands
     </emphasis>
(savannas) and
     <emphasis effect="italics">
temperate grasslands
     </emphasis>
. Tropical grasslands occur in warm climates such as Africa and very limited
regions of Australia. They have a few scattered trees and shrubs, but their
distinct rainy and dry seasons prevent the formation of tropical forests. Most
temperate grasslands are treeless, relatively flat and have rich soil, have
been replaced by farmland.
    </para>
