   <section id="import-auto-id2500202">
    <title>
Succulent Karoo
    </title>
    <para id="import-auto-id2500205">
The Succulent Karoo biome can be found in the west coast of the Northern Cape
Province and the northern parts of the Western Cape Province. This biome is hot
in summer and cold in winter, although the rainfall in this area is very low.
40% of plant species found here are endemic to this biome. The Namaqualand
region of this biome is famous for its colourful wild flowers. Succulent plants
are able to live through dry seasons by using water stored in their leaves or
stems.
    </para>
