   <section id="import-auto-id2228034">
    <title>
Nama Karoo
    </title>
    <para id="import-auto-id2228037">
The Nama Karoo is the second largest biome in South Africa. It forms the major
part of the Northern Cape Province. It is regarded as a semi-desert area
receiving very little rain. The summers are very hot and the winters are very
cold. The dominant vegetation type is grasses.
    </para>
