    <title>
Thicket
    </title>
    <para id="import-auto-id2457554">
The thicket biome occurs along the coasts of KwaZulu Natal and the Eastern Cape.
Most thickets occur in river valleys. Thickets develop in areas where the
rainfall is fairly high however; there may be dry periods that prevent the
vegetation from developing into forests. The vegetation of this biome includes
short tress, low intertwining shrubs and vines. There are no distinct layers of
trees and shrubs with many large open spaces as found in the forest biome.
    </para>
